items.abstract:
<jats:title>Abstract</jats:title>
<jats:p>In 2011 and 2012, an unusual and so far not described foraging behaviour of two finch species was observed in the Barycz valley, W-Poland. Several times Greenfinches <jats:italic>Carduelis chloris</jats:italic>broke off fresh shoots of Scots pine (<jats:italic>Pinus silvestris</jats:italic>) and then licked up the leaking sap. Afterwards, Goldfinches <jats:italic>Carduelis carduelis</jats:italic> also licked up the sap from the same spot. We hypothesize that both species take advantage of the antiseptic nature of <jats:italic>Pinaceae</jats:italic> sap.</jats:p>
title: Licking Of Pine Sap By Greenfinches Carduelis Chloris And Goldfinches Carduelis Carduelis
